      <p id="switch-bookkeeper-in-brief-text"><strong>Switching bookkeepers</strong> means moving your day-to-day books &mdash; categorizing, reconciling, the monthly close, and reporting &mdash; from whoever does it now to a new provider, while keeping your own QuickBooks file and your full history. Because the company file and its data belong to <em>you</em>, a clean switch is mostly an access handoff plus an honest review of the state the books are in. The most common reasons businesses move are a bookkeeper who&rsquo;s falling behind, gone unresponsive, or stepping away &mdash; but not every frustration means you should switch. Sometimes the issue is fixable in place, or your current bookkeeper is a fine fit for simpler needs. The free file review is how you tell the difference objectively.</p>
